snippet: The remains of Lt. Jeffrey Walz were collected before May 2002 but were retested and identified only recently, the city medical examiner’s office said.
abstract: New York City medical examiner's office says remains of Lt Jeffrey Walz, firefighter killed in September 11 attacks, have been identified more than 11 years after his death at the World Trade Center; announcement brings number of identified victims to 1,637.
lead_paragraph: The remains of Lt. Jeffrey Walz were collected before May 2002 but were retested and identified only recently, the city medical examiner’s office said.
